      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The theory that broad tax cuts stimulate growth, often referred to as supply-side economics, is a legitimate, though heavily debated, economic framework. However, in the context of recent wealth data, the argument that these specific cuts translate into widespread, broad-based growth is increasingly being challenged by empirical evidence. Many modern economists view the investment claims as a political justification because the data suggests the benefits are highly concentrated and fail to trickle down effectively.",
      "source": "target",
